    termsText: "The general terms and conditions of business of the online platform Drazba.si regulate the rights and obligations of sellers and bidders.\nThe platform acts exclusively as an information service intermediary, enabling users to publish and view listings/auctions and conclude purchase agreements between the seller and the buyer.\n\n1. Binding offers:\nEvery submitted bid is legally binding. Withdrawal or cancellation of an offer is not possible. In the event of winning an auction, the buyer undertakes to pay the achieved price of the item.\n\n2. Limitation of platform liability:\nDrazba.si (platform services) is not an owner, seller, buyer, and does not represent either of them in concluding sales contracts. The platform does not verify the accuracy or truthfulness of the information provided by users, nor does it give any guarantees regarding the actual material and legal condition of the sold items.\nIn the event that a seller sells a product that does not meet the buyer's expectations, and these unexpected defects were not publicly and visibly stated in the description of the auctioned item before the auction ends, the platform IN NO CASE bears any legal, material or penal responsibility for such purchases. The seller exclusively guarantees and is responsible for the type, quality, characteristics, and legality of the product. The platform operates merely as a technical intermediary of the online service. Any disputes are to be resolved exclusively between the buyer and the seller.\n\n3. As-is system:\nAuctions on the platform are mostly conducted on the 'as-is' principle unless the seller states otherwise. It is the buyer's responsibility to make an inquiry or inspect the item in a timely manner prior to submitting a bid.\n\n4. Breach of contract:\nFailure to pay the purchase price is considered a severe breach of contract and platform terms of business. The platform reserves the right to exclude the user and seek sanctions in court.",
    privacyText: "In accordance with the GDPR regulation, we protect your data with the highest security standards.\nData is used strictly and exclusively for the purposes of conducting auctions, securely and legitimately connecting buyers and sellers, and verifying user identity to prevent abuse.\n\nThe platform may forward your essential contact and identification data solely to the opposing party upon the successful conclusion of an auction expressly for the purpose of carrying out the purchase or conclusion of a legal transaction.\nYour personal data will in no other cases be disclosed to unauthorized third parties without your explicit personal consent or a court order.",
    howText: "Drazba.si is an online real-time digital auction system.\nTo participate, you must successfully:\n1. Register a user account,\n2. Perform verification.\n\nBidding system and rules:\n• Any registered user can bid on any item.\n• Every bid overcome in the last minute before the end of the auction AUTOMATICALLY EXTENDS the auction for an additional 2 minutes, which prevents abuse ('sniping') and provides equal opportunities to all bidders.\n• The winner is the one with the highest bid at the actual expiration time of the auction.",
